Document: PanoramaSkyMaterial
Path: godot/classes/class_panoramaskymaterial.rst
Summary: A resource used to draw a background in Godot, utilizing an equirectangular sky map instead of a cubemap.

A resource referenced in a Sky that is used to draw a background. PanoramaSkyMaterial functions similar to skyboxes in other engines, except it uses an equirectangular sky map instead of a Cubemap. Using an HDR panorama is strongly recommended for accurate, high-quality reflections. Godot supports the Radiance HDR (.hdr) and OpenEXR (.exr) image formats for this purpose. You can use this tool to convert a cubemap to an equirectangular sky map.
---CHUNK---
Document: PanoramaSkyMaterial
Path: godot/classes/class_panoramaskymaterial.rst
Summary: Properties of the PanoramaSkyMaterial class including energy multiplier, filter setting, and panorama texture.

Property: energy_multiplier (float): Scales the overall energy of the sky. Default: 1.0
Property: filter (bool): Enables or disables color filtering for the sky. Default: true
Property: panorama (Texture2D): The panoramic texture used to generate the sky appearance. Default: none
---CHUNK---
Document: PanoramaSkyMaterial  
Path: godot/classes/class_panoramaskymaterial.rst  
Summary: Properties and methods for configuring a PanoramaSkyMaterial in Godot, including brightness control, texture filtering, and panorama texture assignment.  

Property: energy_multiplier (float): The sky's overall brightness multiplier. Higher values result in a brighter sky. Default: 1.0. Method: set_energy_multiplier(value: float). Method: get_energy_multiplier() → float.  
Property: filter (bool): A boolean value to determine if the background texture should be filtered or not. Default: true. Method: set_filtering_enabled(value: bool). Method: is_filtering_enabled() → bool.  
Property: panorama (Texture2D): Texture2D to be applied to the PanoramaSkyMaterial. Method: set_panorama(value: Texture2D). Method: get_panorama() → Texture2D.